    "comment_id": "7437554908339462144",
    "text": "The compounding argument is the real one...and it's the one most founders will have a harder time sitting with. Compounding requires conviction before evidence. That's a hard ask when the quarter is slow and the board wants a dashboard that moves. Meta gives you the illusion of control while podcast gives you an asset that appreciates. Most founders pick the one they can measure today over the one that's still paying them back a year from now.",
